From: Gilly1970 <gilroyscott1970@gmail.com>
Subject: [PATCH] net: airoha: sync UPDMEM source MAC for offloaded IPv6 flows

IPv6 flow entries have no room for an inline source MAC: unlike IPv4, which
stores the full address in the entry, they only carry a 4-bit smac_id and the
hardware builds the L2 header from UPDMEM[smac_id] at transmit time.

UPDMEM is only written from airoha_ppe_init_upd_mem(), whose sole caller is
airoha_set_macaddr() - reachable only from the airoha net_device's own
ndo_set_mac_address. Setting the MAC on a stacked device instead goes through
that device's ndo (e.g. vlan_dev_set_mac_address for an 8021q upper) and never
reaches the airoha driver, so the UPDMEM slot keeps the address of the base
device.

That is harmless while the upper inherits the base MAC, but a VLAN upper with a
cloned MAC address makes the hardware transmit offloaded IPv6 with the stale
base address while IPv4 - which carries the correct address inline - keeps
working. On a MAC-bound ISP the mismatched IPv6 frames are dropped upstream and
the flow black-holes as soon as it is promoted to hardware; disabling hardware
offload restores it because the software path uses the net_device address.

Fix it by keeping the slot in sync with the source MAC the offloaded flow is
actually going to use, which the flow dissector already provides and which
airoha_ppe_flow_offload_replace() has already validated. Cache the programmed
value per port so the register write only happens when it changes.

Reported-by: tompointexe
Signed-off-by: Gilly1970 <gilroyscott1970@gmail.com>
---
--- a/drivers/net/ethernet/airoha/airoha_eth.h
+++ b/drivers/net/ethernet/airoha/airoha_eth.h
@@ -605,6 +605,9 @@
 	int id;
 	int users;
 
+	/* source MAC currently programmed in UPDMEM[id] */
+	u8 smac[ETH_ALEN];
+
 	/* protect concurrent hw_stats and frag register accesses */
 	spinlock_t lock;
 
--- a/drivers/net/ethernet/airoha/airoha_ppe.c
+++ b/drivers/net/ethernet/airoha/airoha_ppe.c
@@ -339,6 +339,21 @@
 	br->src_mac_lo = get_unaligned_be32(eh->h_source + 2);
 }
 
+/* IPv6 flow entries have no room for an inline source MAC: the hw builds the
+ * L2 header from UPDMEM[smac_id] instead. That table is only refreshed when the
+ * MAC of the airoha net_device itself is set, so a stacked device carrying a
+ * different MAC (e.g. a VLAN upper with a cloned address) would make the hw
+ * transmit IPv6 with a stale source MAC. Keep the slot in sync with the address
+ * the offloaded flow actually egresses with.
+ */
+static void airoha_ppe_sync_upd_mem(struct airoha_gdm_dev *dev, const u8 *addr)
+{
+	if (ether_addr_equal(dev->port->smac, addr))
+		return;
+
+	airoha_ppe_init_upd_mem(dev, addr);
+}
+
 static int airoha_ppe_foe_entry_prepare(struct airoha_eth *eth,
 					struct airoha_foe_entry *hwe,
 					struct net_device *netdev, int type,
@@ -416,6 +431,9 @@
 						  dsa_port);
 
 			smac_id = port->id;
+			if (type >= PPE_PKT_TYPE_IPV6_ROUTE_3T)
+				airoha_ppe_sync_upd_mem(dev,
+							data->eth.h_source);
 		}
 	}
 
@@ -1545,6 +1563,8 @@
 		     FIELD_PREP(PPE_UPDMEM_ADDR_MASK, port->id) |
 		     FIELD_PREP(PPE_UPDMEM_OFFSET_MASK, 1) |
 		     PPE_UPDMEM_WR_MASK | PPE_UPDMEM_REQ_MASK);
+
+	ether_addr_copy(port->smac, addr);
 }
 
 struct airoha_ppe_dev *airoha_ppe_get_dev(struct device *dev)
